## C Basics
C is a compiled language. You must compile the code before running it. We use `printf` from `<stdio.h>` for output.
```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
    return 0;
}
```

## Variables & Types
C requires explicit types. `printf` uses format specifiers like `%d` (int) and `%f` (float).
```c
int age = 20;
printf("Age: %d", age);
```

