lessons.theory:
## Pointers
Pointers store memory addresses. `&` gets an address. `*` dereferences an address to get the value.
```c
int x = 10;
int *ptr = &x;
printf("%d", *ptr);
```

lessons.starterCode:
#include <stdio.h>

